               <head>Miscellaneous Sufi works, 7 works (a-g)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of Arabic and Persian works on Sufism, presently incomplete and defective at the end. Although the volume is not date, item B dates to 15 Rabīʿ al-Avval RY 15 of Emperor Muḥammad Shāh (1145)/5 September 1732. Red IOL leather binding; net overlay on many folios. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1083-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="26r">ff. 1v-26r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Meditations and counsels in prose and verse to those on the Ṣūfī path. 
</p>
                        <p>Author not identified. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is divided into thirty-one marḥalah. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Rough shikastah āmīz on alternating tinted papers. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21622">Ṭarīq al-ḥaqīqah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21622">طريق الحقيقة</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000152" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1083-item2">
                     <locus from="27v" to="49v">ff. 27v-49v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">Jāmī, 1414-1492 </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">نور الدين عبد الرحمن جامى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Definitions and explanations of Ṣūfī terms and doctrines with illustrative rubāʿī poems conventionally entitled <title>Lavāʾiḥ</title>, by the celebrated mystic, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997" role="aut">ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Jāmī</persName>, whose name does not appear until the end. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 49v): 15 Rabīʿ al-Avval RY 15 of <persName key="viaf_45680638" role="oth">Emperor Muḥammad Shāh</persName> (1145)/5 September 1732. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Rough shikastah āmīz on alternating tinted papers. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008118219" n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1083-item3">
                     <locus from="50v" to="51r">ff. 50v-51r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Fragmentary excerpt of an unidentified treatise on the unity or tawḥīd of God. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated. 
</p>
                        <p>Rough shikastah āmīz on alternating tinted papers. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008118218" n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1083-item4">
                     <locus from="52v" to="80r">ff. 52v-80r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Excerpt of the first chapter from the <title>Kashf al-ḥaqāʾiq</title> (consisting of seven chapters) dealing with divine substance and the materiality of spiritual phenomena by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658820.0x000001 viaf_84084776" role="aut">ʿAzīz ibn Muḥammad al-Naṣafī al-Bukhārī</persName> (d. 661/1263). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated. 
</p>
                        <p>Ends with a short Arabic prayer in bold naskh script. 
</p>
                        <p>Rough shikastah āmīz on alternating tinted papers. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21623">Kashf al-ḥaqāʾiq</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21623">کشف الحقائق</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658820.0x000001 viaf_84084776" type="supplied" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">ʿAzīz ibn Muḥammad al-Naṣafī al-Bukhārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658820.0x000001 viaf_84084776">نسفى، عزيز الدين بن محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1083-item5">
                     <locus from="80v" to="83r">ff. 80v-83r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Excerpt of the <persName>
                              <title>Burhān al-ʿāshiqīn</title>
                           </persName> of Shaykh Sharaf al-Dīn ibn Aḥmad Yaḥyá Manīrī (d. 782/1380). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated. 
</p>
                        <p>Rough shikastah āmīz on alternating tinted papers. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21631">Burhān al-ʿāshiqīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21631">برهان العاشقین</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658756.0x000001 viaf_74159218">Shaykh Sharaf al-Dīn ibn Aḥmad Yaḥyá Manīrī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658756.0x000001 viaf_74159218">شرف الدين احمد يحيى منيرى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85085934" n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1083-item6">
                     <locus from="83v" to="85r">ff. 83v-85r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item f. </p>
                        <p>Excerpt from an unspecified work by Shaykh Sharaf al-Dīn ibn Aḥmad Yaḥyá Manīrī (d. 782/1380) on the miracles or karāmāt of saints. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated. 
</p>
                        <p>Rough shikastah āmīz on alternating tinted papers. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is followed by a series of short excerpts on Sufism and Arabic prayers, some written obliquely, including the named works <title>Kashf al-maḥjūb</title>, the <title>Munājāt</title> of <persName key="viaf_19703891" role="ant">ʿAbd Allāh Anṣārī</persName>, a work on Arabic grammar, a work attributed to <persName key="person_f7594" role="ant">Shaykh Muḥammad Bukhārī</persName>, a tradition relating to <persName key="viaf_90045570" role="ant">Ḥasan Baṣrī</persName>, a Naqshbandī work, medicinal preparations, recipes for food, magic squares, and an Arabic prayer (ff. 85v-102r). 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658756.0x000001 viaf_74159218" type="supplied">Shaykh Sharaf al-Dīn ibn Aḥmad Yaḥyá Manīrī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658756.0x000001 viaf_74159218" type="supplied">شرف الدين احمد يحيى منيرى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000152" n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1083-item7">
                     <locus from="102v" to="133v">ff. 102v-133v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item g. </p>
                        <p>Untitled critical commentary on Ṣufī doctrines reported by the disciples of the Naqshbandī leader, <persName key="viaf_314814912" role="ant">Khvājah Muḥammad Bāqī ibn ʿAbd al-Salām</persName> (d. 1012/1603), by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is followed by the beginning of another excerpt that continued onto subsequent folios, which are now missing. This indicated that this volume is presently incomplete and defective. 
</p>
                        <p>Rough shikastah āmīz on alternating tinted papers. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
